WEBVTT

00:21.369 --> 00:22.805
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

00:26.243 --> 00:27.897
[GASPING]

00:36.297 --> 00:37.602
[GRUNTING]

00:55.403 --> 00:56.752
[GASPING]

00:57.927 --> 00:59.450
No! No!

01:00.669 --> 01:03.106
Please stop! Please!

01:03.150 --> 01:04.412
[YELPING]

01:07.241 --> 01:08.546
[SCREAMS]

01:11.984 --> 01:13.595
[SOBBING]

01:17.990 --> 01:19.688
CAL: Emily! Emily!

01:19.731 --> 01:23.257
No! No! No!

01:23.300 --> 01:25.694
Emily! Hey! Hey!

01:29.437 --> 01:31.091
[SHUSHING]
[GASPING]

01:32.570 --> 01:33.702
I'm right here.

01:38.402 --> 01:41.971
It's okay.
Breathe. Breathe.

01:42.014 --> 01:43.581
[SOBBING]

01:47.933 --> 01:49.326
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

01:52.938 --> 01:54.549
[CONTINUES SHUSHING]

01:58.596 --> 01:59.945
[CRYING]

02:12.044 --> 02:13.133
He had Flynn.

02:14.830 --> 02:16.875
He had Flynn.
He had Flynn
all this time.

02:16.919 --> 02:18.094
Who had Flynn?

02:18.703 --> 02:20.227
Oduwale had Flynn.

02:23.491 --> 02:25.101
Come on, Em,
can you walk?

02:25.884 --> 02:26.929
Okay.

02:28.583 --> 02:29.758
Can you stand up?

02:30.715 --> 02:31.803
Okay.
Yeah.

02:33.414 --> 02:35.067
Hey.
I got it.

02:37.766 --> 02:39.028
[SNIFFLES]

02:41.291 --> 02:42.510
I got it.

02:43.772 --> 02:44.860
Come on.

02:47.993 --> 02:49.430
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

02:58.265 --> 03:02.269
Hey.
Nick, we're looking
into Oduwale.

03:02.312 --> 03:05.010
I need your help.
I need you to keep
him away from Flynn.

03:06.360 --> 03:07.622
What's going on?
EMILY: I don't know.

03:07.665 --> 03:09.667
I'll call you as soon as
we find out more.

03:09.711 --> 03:11.147
Okay.
EMILY: Just promise me

03:11.191 --> 03:12.801
you'll keep Flynn
away from him.

03:13.976 --> 03:15.717
Of course. I promise.

03:15.760 --> 03:16.892
Thanks.

03:17.893 --> 03:18.937
Yeah.

03:21.201 --> 03:22.506
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

03:27.990 --> 03:29.209
[ENGINE STARTS]

03:39.915 --> 03:43.397
Hey. [SIGHS]
Um, Emily called.

03:44.441 --> 03:46.051
She's looking into
Dr. Oduwale.

03:47.836 --> 03:50.491
Are you serious?
What for?

03:51.361 --> 03:52.928
I don't know.

03:52.971 --> 03:54.190
She's investigating him.

03:55.800 --> 03:59.587
I know you and Dr. Oduwale
are colleagues,

03:59.630 --> 04:02.198
but I agreed
to keep Flynn away
from him for now.

04:03.373 --> 04:05.201
I hope that's okay.

04:05.245 --> 04:06.811
I mean,
it's probably nothing.

04:06.855 --> 04:10.598
I'm sure it's nothing,
but if it puts
your mind at ease...

04:12.513 --> 04:13.601
Thank you.

04:14.950 --> 04:16.821
I know I don't
say it enough,

04:16.865 --> 04:20.434
but I really appreciate
the way that you handle
our family dynamic...

04:20.477 --> 04:22.131
I love you,
and I love Flynn.

04:23.132 --> 04:24.176
It's that simple.

04:29.399 --> 04:30.574
[CHUCKLES]

04:33.098 --> 04:34.317
I love you.

04:50.072 --> 04:51.291
Dr. Oduwale.

04:53.423 --> 04:54.424
Emily.

04:56.208 --> 04:58.472
[STAMMERS]
This is a surprise.

04:58.515 --> 05:01.562
I don't have a session
with Flynn for a few days.

05:03.128 --> 05:04.260
Is something wrong?

05:06.915 --> 05:08.395
No. No.

05:11.093 --> 05:12.921
Nothing like that. Um...
[SIGHS]

05:17.273 --> 05:19.623
I need to ask you
a few questions.
[SNIFFLES]

05:20.232 --> 05:22.017
[DOOR CLOSES]

05:22.060 --> 05:25.281
Which I would love
to answer, but, um,
I have some appointments.

05:25.325 --> 05:26.761
It's not gonna
take very long.

05:31.418 --> 05:33.942
Did you ever
work on something
called Project Quill?

05:36.161 --> 05:37.380
[SIGHS] Uh...

05:39.469 --> 05:40.862
Project Quill.

05:41.558 --> 05:42.733
[CHUCKLES]

05:44.692 --> 05:47.651
That's a...
That's a name I haven't
heard in years.

05:48.043 --> 05:49.218
And?

05:52.003 --> 05:53.875
Did you work there?

05:53.918 --> 05:58.358
No. Well, not in
any official capacity.

05:58.401 --> 06:00.621
So what capacity
did you work on it?

06:02.840 --> 06:07.932
Building 60 was
a psychobiology hub.

06:09.543 --> 06:12.633
The idea was that, uh,

06:12.676 --> 06:17.246
students and faculty
would talk over
ping-pong tables.

06:20.336 --> 06:21.424
That's all it was?

06:23.426 --> 06:24.427
Just talk?

06:26.647 --> 06:27.735
Mostly.

06:29.476 --> 06:34.394
I'm sure there were
those looking to apply
their theories,

06:35.830 --> 06:37.484
but it never amounted
to very much.

06:47.015 --> 06:49.409
EMILY: Did you
ever work on any of
the experiments there?

06:54.152 --> 06:56.633
I might have taken part
in some of the discussions,

06:58.156 --> 07:02.770
but I can't recall
any specific conversations.

07:02.813 --> 07:04.032
It was 30 years ago.

07:05.120 --> 07:07.035
I'd just finished my thesis.

07:09.080 --> 07:11.343
It's all a blur.

07:23.181 --> 07:24.531
Would you like some water?

07:34.671 --> 07:35.803
No.

07:41.112 --> 07:42.157
No.

07:50.208 --> 07:54.343
Emily, have you considered
taking some private sessions

07:54.386 --> 07:55.562
just for yourself?

07:56.693 --> 07:58.652
It wouldn't have
to be with me.

07:58.695 --> 08:01.698
There are other
specialists working here.

08:01.742 --> 08:05.528
No, thank you. I've [SIGHS]
tried the whole therapy thing.

08:10.228 --> 08:11.403
It didn't take.

08:15.146 --> 08:16.408
Well, I'm sorry.

08:21.544 --> 08:22.893
And I'm sorry to have to

08:22.937 --> 08:24.765
cut short this trip
down memory lane,

08:24.808 --> 08:27.115
but I have to go.

08:33.600 --> 08:34.992
[SNIFFLES]

08:42.522 --> 08:46.134
That's a very
interesting piece.
Who's the artist?

08:46.177 --> 08:47.657
One of my patients.

08:55.622 --> 08:58.538
Let me know if you
change your mind about
the private sessions.

08:59.930 --> 09:03.151
Felicia can always book you
in for an appointment.

09:03.194 --> 09:04.718
Felicia.
Doctor.

09:14.684 --> 09:16.904
Hi, Felicia.
Ms. Byrne.

09:19.341 --> 09:21.517
Could I get Dr. Oduwale's
schedule for the next week?

09:21.561 --> 09:24.999
I need to set up
a few appointments.FELICIA: Hmm. Okay.

09:25.042 --> 09:29.612
Maybe I could
come back later today.Uh, no, he's not here.

09:29.656 --> 09:31.919
He's at Fort Devens
all day every Wednesday.

09:33.485 --> 09:35.226
Fort Devens?

09:35.270 --> 09:37.315
FELICIA: Yeah, he has
a private practice there also.

09:38.621 --> 09:40.144
For the soldiers?

09:40.188 --> 09:43.583
Uh, yeah, he does
trauma group, uh,
private sessions.

09:43.626 --> 09:44.758
For over 10 years now.

09:45.280 --> 09:46.281
Thanks.

09:52.374 --> 09:56.596
Fort Devens was the base
Rex Wolfe was stationed at
before his deployment.

09:56.639 --> 09:58.293
They could've crossed
paths back then.

09:58.336 --> 10:00.382
And Oduwale could have
pulled him into
his experiments

10:00.425 --> 10:02.819
when he needed
somebody with Rex's
special skills.

10:02.863 --> 10:04.952
Mmm-hmm.

10:04.995 --> 10:08.216
The thing is,
is that Oduwale is
not listed on record

10:08.259 --> 10:10.740
as Rex's doctor in any
of his military files.

10:10.784 --> 10:12.394
Yeah, they wouldn't be.

10:12.437 --> 10:15.310
They keep the medical
records separate from
the service records.

10:17.704 --> 10:18.661
[BEEPING]

10:19.793 --> 10:20.750
[OBJECT THUDS]

10:37.941 --> 10:39.029
Hey.

10:39.769 --> 10:40.770
Hey.

10:42.903 --> 10:43.904
You good?

10:44.687 --> 10:45.993
Yeah. You?

10:46.646 --> 10:47.734
I am now.

10:50.954 --> 10:55.350
Listen, uh, I was thinking,
it's been a while

10:55.393 --> 10:57.439
since I've been
in a relationship,

10:57.482 --> 11:01.312
or one that's not
self-destructive.
And, um...

11:04.185 --> 11:07.449
I saw this, and I
couldn't help myself.

11:08.711 --> 11:10.060
Oh, Jack.

11:11.018 --> 11:12.323
Open it.

11:20.027 --> 11:20.984
It's your birthstone.

11:24.945 --> 11:25.989
Do you like it?

11:26.947 --> 11:27.948
Yeah, it's beautiful.

11:29.993 --> 11:32.256
But I...
I can't keep it.

11:33.475 --> 11:35.520
Oh, yeah, yeah,
I know. Uh...

11:35.564 --> 11:38.088
I was thinking maybe
you could say you
bought it for yourself.

11:40.700 --> 11:41.701
I suppose.

11:44.225 --> 11:45.400
What's going on?

11:47.576 --> 11:48.708
Nick knows.

11:51.580 --> 11:53.234
Not about you
but he knows.

11:54.539 --> 11:55.540
Uh...

11:56.716 --> 11:58.239
Okay. Um...

11:59.066 --> 12:00.241
Okay.

12:01.764 --> 12:02.896
What do you want to do?

12:05.202 --> 12:06.334
I can't keep lying.

12:11.208 --> 12:12.253
You want to stop.

12:13.123 --> 12:14.342
I'm sorry.

12:15.430 --> 12:17.171
But...

12:17.214 --> 12:20.609
I have a lot more
to lose than you do.
My marriage, my family.

12:20.652 --> 12:22.785
Yeah. Thanks for pointing
that out, Alice. I actually
have a sister and a father

12:22.829 --> 12:24.221
who would be pissed
as hell...

12:25.222 --> 12:26.310
Hi.
Hi.

12:44.851 --> 12:46.678
Look, can we maybe please
just get together later

12:46.722 --> 12:48.289
and talk about this, please?

12:48.332 --> 12:49.769
I think we covered
everything.

13:03.217 --> 13:05.001
Hey.

13:05.045 --> 13:09.005
Dr. Oduwale
treated Rex Wolfe at
the VA long enough

13:09.049 --> 13:11.703
for a significant
doctor-patient relationship
to develop.

13:17.013 --> 13:19.494
But don't let me
interrupt you.

13:19.537 --> 13:22.497
Sorry, Oduwale wrote
a number of papers
when he was at Saugus,

13:22.540 --> 13:24.412
and they're all online.

13:24.455 --> 13:26.370
And you plan on wading
through them how?

13:34.335 --> 13:35.379
By ignoring me.

13:37.468 --> 13:39.253
[WHISPERS] What?
Okay, tell me.

13:41.385 --> 13:43.213
Citations.

13:43.257 --> 13:47.087
Oduwale had independent access
to Catalyst Diagnostics'
database in 1982,

13:47.130 --> 13:49.829
and then again here,
he cites it in 2013.

13:49.872 --> 13:51.831
Thirty-one years.

13:51.874 --> 13:53.963
We need access
to that database.Mmm-hmm.

13:54.007 --> 13:55.791
We need to see
what Tommy found.

13:55.835 --> 13:57.140
I'll push
that warrant through.

14:07.672 --> 14:09.152
You want printouts
of these files,

14:09.196 --> 14:10.893
or do you just want
to look at them on
the computer screen?

14:10.937 --> 14:12.590
The printouts
would be best.

14:12.634 --> 14:15.071
Any of the six names
that you have
in the database.

14:16.768 --> 14:19.119
MAN: Usually, we don't
let anybody into the archive,

14:19.162 --> 14:22.426
but warrants have a funny way
of opening doors.

14:24.515 --> 14:26.082
Oh, wow.

14:26.126 --> 14:27.997
Tyler Brandon Mills?

14:28.041 --> 14:29.433
I thought that
was all over.

14:37.920 --> 14:39.226
Score.

14:39.269 --> 14:40.488
I'm getting all six.

14:41.968 --> 14:44.971
[PRINTER WHIRRING]

14:45.014 --> 14:47.799
What do you think?
EMILY: I'll see what else
they have in common.

14:52.587 --> 14:53.675
Okay.

14:56.286 --> 14:57.287
Thank you.

14:58.462 --> 14:59.507
Here.

15:02.162 --> 15:04.686
Tyler's barely
in here. Look.

15:04.729 --> 15:07.602
Nothing since childhood.
No regular treatments.

15:07.645 --> 15:09.212
Looks like he's
a dead end.No.

15:09.256 --> 15:11.867
No, he's a part
of the pattern.How?

15:11.911 --> 15:13.564
The violence, the hives.

15:13.608 --> 15:14.870
MAN: Here are the other ones.

15:14.914 --> 15:16.654
There's gotta be
missing data.

15:16.698 --> 15:18.918
How long do you keep
patients' files stored?

15:19.440 --> 15:20.920
Uh, depends.

15:20.963 --> 15:23.531
Could be a few years.
Could be decades.

15:23.574 --> 15:25.098
Could be indefinitely.

15:25.141 --> 15:27.535
We keep medical records,
but we're also
the largest biobank

15:27.578 --> 15:30.451
on the East Coast.
CAL: Biobank?

15:30.494 --> 15:34.063
So, someone could
have access to blood
samples from years ago?

15:34.107 --> 15:35.630
Not just blood.

15:35.673 --> 15:38.981
We keep samples
of urine, skin samples,
organ tissue.

15:39.025 --> 15:40.678
Anything that's left over
from routine tests.

15:40.722 --> 15:42.506
You know, biopsies,
etcetera.

15:42.550 --> 15:46.075
Why?
It's an enormous
resource for research.

15:46.119 --> 15:49.470
Ever since the late '90s
when genetic testing
became more sophisticated,

15:49.513 --> 15:52.168
these samples, they're
way too valuable
to just discard.

15:53.387 --> 15:55.084
Cal.
Is that everything
you need?

15:56.216 --> 15:57.217
For now.

16:05.225 --> 16:08.489
WOMAN ON PA:
Dr. Hughes to the NICU.
Dr. Hughes to the NICU.

16:10.012 --> 16:11.057
ALICE: Emily.

16:13.537 --> 16:17.150
Hey, are you
leaving early?Uh, errands.

16:17.193 --> 16:18.412
Can we talk
for a second?

16:18.934 --> 16:20.109
Okay.

16:20.153 --> 16:21.545
Do you mind
if we talk here?

16:23.591 --> 16:24.722
Sure, yeah.

16:24.766 --> 16:26.159
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

16:30.511 --> 16:32.078
You need to get that?
No.

16:32.774 --> 16:34.210
Uh...

16:34.254 --> 16:37.257
What's happening
with Dr. Oduwale?
Nick told me.

16:37.300 --> 16:39.128
Is there something
I should know about?

16:39.911 --> 16:41.348
We're not sure just yet,

16:41.391 --> 16:43.785
but you used to work
for him for a while, right?

16:43.828 --> 16:45.526
Yeah, for years.

16:45.569 --> 16:47.571
Did you ever hear
anything bad about him?

16:47.615 --> 16:49.095
No. Never.

16:49.138 --> 16:51.401
We're very fortunate
that he's agreed
to see Flynn.

16:51.445 --> 16:52.489
Yeah.

16:53.186 --> 16:55.492
I mean, of course.

16:55.536 --> 16:58.930
But what about,
I mean, his ethics
regarding patients?

16:58.974 --> 17:02.195
Did he ever
bend the rules?
Anything like that?

17:02.238 --> 17:04.327
No. He would
never do that.

17:06.373 --> 17:07.896
You really like him,
don't you?

17:09.115 --> 17:10.159
I admire him.

17:12.727 --> 17:16.774
He published
a paper in 2013
about blood chemistry,

17:16.818 --> 17:19.864
and it's connected
to something that
the FBI is looking into.

17:19.908 --> 17:23.042
Being very thorough.
Yeah.

17:23.085 --> 17:26.393
I mean, of course.
It has to do with Flynn.

17:26.436 --> 17:29.918
Listen, Emily,
if you find anything
that could affect Flynn...

17:29.961 --> 17:31.789
We'll call you right away.
I promise.

17:35.750 --> 17:37.317
Alice, um...

17:39.449 --> 17:43.105
Thank you for everything
that you've done for Flynn,

17:43.149 --> 17:45.325
for being there for him
for all these years.

17:46.630 --> 17:48.023
He's lucky to have you.

17:49.242 --> 17:50.243
We all are.

17:51.200 --> 17:52.375
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

17:52.941 --> 17:54.073
Thanks.

18:17.183 --> 18:18.314
Hey.
Hey.

18:18.358 --> 18:20.664
What's going on
with Dr. Oduwale?

18:20.708 --> 18:22.971
If there's anything
I can do to help, I can...

18:23.014 --> 18:24.407
Yeah.

18:24.451 --> 18:26.583
Nick, we're trying
to connect him
to your case.

18:27.628 --> 18:29.499
Uh, Tyler Brandon Mills?

18:31.327 --> 18:32.328
How?
[SIGHS]

18:34.765 --> 18:36.550
Come on. Follow me.

18:42.469 --> 18:43.948
Hey, you wanna
come over here?

18:47.474 --> 18:48.562
NICK: What's going on, Isaac?

18:50.041 --> 18:54.263
We think Dr. Oduwale
ordered Rex Wolfe
to kill TBM.

18:59.268 --> 19:01.270
What?

19:01.314 --> 19:05.579
Oduwale got to know
Rex Wolfe during therapy
sessions at Fort Devens,

19:05.622 --> 19:07.885
and then used him
to do the fentanyl murders.

19:09.322 --> 19:10.279
[SIGHS]

19:19.027 --> 19:20.159
That's...

19:25.642 --> 19:27.818
Hey, hey...
That piece of shit.

19:27.862 --> 19:28.863
I know.

19:30.821 --> 19:32.562
He was working
with Flynn for months.

19:33.433 --> 19:34.390
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

19:36.523 --> 19:38.525
It's...

19:41.615 --> 19:42.659
Hey.

19:43.399 --> 19:44.444
I...

19:48.796 --> 19:51.146
I'm... The...
We... We, um...

19:52.582 --> 19:54.584
We subpoenaed Rex Wolfe's
phone records

19:55.759 --> 19:57.544
right after he killed TBM.

19:57.587 --> 20:00.938
We figured we could get
something from them
like a friend or a colleague

20:00.982 --> 20:04.333
who helped him hide.
Let me guess.
He had no friends.

20:05.900 --> 20:09.860
Or they were all big fans
of burner phones.

20:09.904 --> 20:12.733
We got nothing.
That's a red flag
right there.

20:12.776 --> 20:17.041
Listen, Nick, did TBM's
parents mention anything about
routine medical treatments?

20:17.085 --> 20:18.869
All the vics had them.

20:18.913 --> 20:21.742
See, Oduwale used
these treatments to
cover for his experiments.

20:21.785 --> 20:22.917
Jesus.

20:23.570 --> 20:24.788
[CLEARS THROAT]

20:27.356 --> 20:29.402
We need to talk to the Mills.
I can go.

20:29.445 --> 20:32.492
No, no, no.
I'll handle it.

20:34.015 --> 20:35.190
It's my case.

20:38.019 --> 20:39.150
Thanks.

20:57.430 --> 21:00.302
Thank you for agreeing
to see me, Mrs. Mills.

21:00.346 --> 21:01.869
I wouldn't be here
if it wasn't imperative.

21:01.912 --> 21:03.610
Let's just make
this quick.

21:03.653 --> 21:05.829
The last time I was here,
you mentioned sending
your son...

21:05.873 --> 21:07.309
His name is Tyler.

21:09.006 --> 21:11.357
You mentioned
sending Tyler
to group therapy.

21:12.053 --> 21:13.446
[TV PLAYING INSIDE]

21:14.360 --> 21:16.362
There were, uh...

21:16.405 --> 21:19.190
There was an informal
one that helped.

21:19.234 --> 21:20.627
They met at the hospital.

21:22.759 --> 21:25.545
I'm sorry. I'm sorry,
I don't remember much.

21:25.588 --> 21:29.200
He was physically
quite healthy, right?

21:29.244 --> 21:32.029
Yes.
We've reviewed
Tyler's medical records.

21:32.073 --> 21:36.295
We didn't find any
recurring health treatments.

21:36.338 --> 21:39.515
He was never given any
psychotropic medications?

21:43.084 --> 21:45.304
Um, we...

21:46.392 --> 21:47.741
We never went
down that route.

21:47.784 --> 21:49.569
My husband is
completely against it.

21:52.136 --> 21:53.312
Mrs. Mills...

21:56.227 --> 21:58.665
Sometimes when
nothing else works,

21:59.274 --> 22:00.971
we do things.

22:01.015 --> 22:04.323
We take calculated risks,

22:04.366 --> 22:07.369
hoping that it will
pay off for our kids.

22:09.589 --> 22:10.894
I certainly have.

22:12.809 --> 22:14.898
Could you just...

22:16.770 --> 22:18.032
Yeah, yeah.

22:20.730 --> 22:22.123
[TV CONTINUES PLAYING]

22:29.739 --> 22:33.090
Tyler really connected with

22:33.134 --> 22:35.223
the doctor in that
hospital group.

22:35.266 --> 22:38.792
Now, I never told
Chauncey this,
but the doctor said

22:38.835 --> 22:43.666
that Tyler would dramatically
improve if he started
taking an experimental drug.

22:46.365 --> 22:50.020
He said insurance wouldn't
cover the cost, but he would
give them to Tyler for free.

22:50.064 --> 22:54.808
And Tyler told me
that they made his mind
work like lightning.

22:54.851 --> 22:57.027
Would you be able
to recognize him,

22:57.071 --> 22:58.333
the doctor?

22:58.377 --> 22:59.726
Maybe. I don't know.
Okay.

23:01.510 --> 23:02.642
Was this the man?

23:04.600 --> 23:06.428
Yes, that's him.
Are you sure?

23:10.998 --> 23:14.567
What was in those
injections?I don't know.

23:14.610 --> 23:16.699
Did he turn my son
into a killer?

23:16.743 --> 23:18.005
I can't, I'm sorry...

23:18.048 --> 23:19.136
Please.
I'm sorry. I don't know.

23:19.180 --> 23:20.747
[CRYING] No, please!
I don't know.

23:25.969 --> 23:28.798
CAL: The same person
who ordered Rex Wolfe
to do the fentanyl killings

23:28.842 --> 23:31.584
also ordered Detective
Tommy Gibbs's murder.

23:31.627 --> 23:36.023
Dr. Semo Oduwale
was Rex Wolfe's
therapist at Fort Devens.

23:36.066 --> 23:37.546
We also believe
that he recruited Wolfe

23:37.590 --> 23:39.635
to help conduct
experiments on victims.

23:39.679 --> 23:42.508
CAL: And when those
experiments went south,
he ordered Wolfe to kill them.

23:42.551 --> 23:44.597
"To clean up his mistakes"
was the way Wolfe put it.

23:44.640 --> 23:47.077
This is the first I'm hearing
about experiments.

23:47.121 --> 23:48.905
There were clandestine.

23:48.949 --> 23:51.560
All of the victims
had blood work done
at Catalyst Diagnostics,

23:51.604 --> 23:53.040
which is why
Oduwale picked them.

23:53.083 --> 23:55.216
And we verified
that Oduwale had
access to their database

23:55.259 --> 23:58.306
through Project Quill
since 1982.What's Quill?

23:58.349 --> 24:01.483
It's a psychobiology
think tank run out
of Saugus University.

24:01.527 --> 24:04.007
It was defunded
in the early '90s.We think Oduwale went rogue,

24:04.051 --> 24:05.879
and then he continued
his experiments elsewhere.

24:06.532 --> 24:08.011
On human subjects.

24:08.055 --> 24:11.450
Heather Mills identified
Dr. Oduwale as
her son's therapist.

24:11.493 --> 24:15.454
He apparently injected Tyler
with an experimental drug.

24:15.497 --> 24:19.762
And Detective Tommy Gibbs
connected Oduwale
to Catalyst Diagnostics

24:19.806 --> 24:23.331
and to Project Quill,
so Oduwale had him killed.

24:26.595 --> 24:28.467
We want to bring him in
for questioning.

24:33.472 --> 24:35.865
Do it. Bring him in.

24:35.909 --> 24:38.825
But Julianne and Cal
will handle the interview.

24:41.044 --> 24:43.656
Emily, Nick, given your
connection to Oduwale,

24:43.699 --> 24:45.832
you can't be a part
of that formal process.

24:47.486 --> 24:48.530
Understood.

24:57.147 --> 25:01.195
Dr. Oduwale,
I'm Special Agent Gunnarsen.

25:01.238 --> 25:02.849
This is
Special Agent Isaac.

25:02.892 --> 25:04.677
Thank you
for coming in today.

25:04.720 --> 25:06.635
My pleasure.
If you're ready...

25:06.679 --> 25:08.463
Sure.

25:08.507 --> 25:12.859
Gunnarsen. That's
an interesting name.
What's your background?

25:12.902 --> 25:15.818
I'm guessing Norwegian
or Swedish.You're right.

25:15.862 --> 25:17.690
My paternal grandfather
was from Sweden.

25:19.387 --> 25:20.823
Does this man look familiar?

25:36.796 --> 25:37.840
Oh.

25:38.841 --> 25:40.190
Rex Wolfe.

25:42.236 --> 25:43.716
Yes, I do know him.

25:45.456 --> 25:50.374
But I'm afraid this is
a case of doctor-patient
confidentiality.

25:55.205 --> 25:58.121
Which I would be
willing to waive.

25:58.165 --> 26:00.210
Thank you for understanding.

26:00.254 --> 26:02.561
So I take it Wolfe
was a patient?

26:02.604 --> 26:06.521
At Fort Devens,
about 10 years back.

26:06.565 --> 26:09.568
I treated him for
about five or six months.

26:10.786 --> 26:13.615
He was withdrawn.
Avoidant.

26:14.790 --> 26:16.531
We often sat in silence.

26:18.402 --> 26:21.057
Did your relationship
extend outside the room?

26:21.101 --> 26:22.755
It barely extended inside.

26:24.408 --> 26:26.541
JULIANNE:
Did he ever indicate
violent tendencies?

26:29.109 --> 26:30.110
Never.

26:31.894 --> 26:34.767
Have you had any contact
with Rex in subsequent years?

26:36.769 --> 26:40.076
Not that I can recall.

26:40.120 --> 26:43.297
But I'll admit,
I've treated hundreds
of military personnel.

26:47.649 --> 26:50.652
I'm guessing that Rex
is in some kind of trouble?

26:56.353 --> 27:01.402
I do what I can
for my patients, but
it's not an exact science.

27:03.491 --> 27:04.579
I wish it were.

27:06.407 --> 27:11.630
When I think of Flynn
having private sessions
with him...

27:11.673 --> 27:16.373
ODUWALE: But any
specific conversations...
It was 30 years ago.

27:17.679 --> 27:19.899
So, what do you think?
We have about 90 minutes?

27:22.423 --> 27:23.467
Two hours.

27:26.775 --> 27:28.559
I asked Cal
to slow-play it.

27:30.039 --> 27:31.693
ODUWALE:
Not that I can recall.

27:36.872 --> 27:38.221
[SIGHS]

27:40.920 --> 27:43.879
Back in... This is
before the Gulf War.

27:43.923 --> 27:47.753
CAL: You cited Catalyst
Diagnostics' database

27:47.796 --> 27:50.146
as a resource
for biological data.

27:52.322 --> 27:54.150
How long did you
have access to that?

27:55.108 --> 27:58.415
For the duration of one study.

27:58.459 --> 28:03.246
I was only permitted to
use their data on-site,
under supervision.

28:03.290 --> 28:04.683
They're real sticklers
over there.

28:06.293 --> 28:07.686
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

28:23.223 --> 28:24.180
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

29:08.877 --> 29:09.965
Damn.

29:13.882 --> 29:16.232
Before the recent
events at FEMA,

29:16.276 --> 29:18.887
were you familiar with
Tyler Brandon Mills?

29:22.717 --> 29:25.111
Tyler was my patient
for a time.

29:29.245 --> 29:30.943
Difficult situation.

29:33.380 --> 29:34.685
Tragic outcome.

29:38.428 --> 29:39.952
Did you have anything
to do with it?

29:42.389 --> 29:43.564
Excuse me?

29:46.175 --> 29:48.177
Perhaps it was
the injections you gave him.

29:53.922 --> 29:55.315
Did his mother tell you that?

29:58.492 --> 30:03.018
That poor woman,
she tried everything
in her power to help her son.

30:04.150 --> 30:07.066
She gave him kava extract.

30:07.109 --> 30:11.810
She gave him St. John's wort,
which was disastrous
for his mental state.

30:11.853 --> 30:15.726
Tyler's mother feels
you were the one to
give him some injections

30:15.770 --> 30:17.076
to cure his issues.

30:18.338 --> 30:19.818
Instead,
they made them worse.

30:21.820 --> 30:26.781
Tyler's mother was preyed upon
by charlatans more than once.

30:26.825 --> 30:29.784
Now, sadly, she has
me confused with someone else.

30:29.828 --> 30:33.309
More than once,
I have been the target
of false accusations.

30:36.573 --> 30:38.793
Now, do you have
any more questions?

30:38.837 --> 30:41.752
Unfortunately, I have an
appointment this evening.

30:43.667 --> 30:45.191
Yes.

30:45.234 --> 30:46.757
We have just a few more.

30:48.585 --> 30:50.022
Am I under arrest?

30:50.892 --> 30:52.851
No. Of course not.

30:54.287 --> 30:56.680
Then I have to go.

30:56.724 --> 31:00.293
Please make an appointment
with Ms. Crandall
at the hospital,

31:00.336 --> 31:03.774
if you'd like to schedule
in another discussion.

31:04.297 --> 31:05.820
[DOOR BUZZES]

31:05.864 --> 31:07.822
I sincerely hope
you find whoever it is
you're looking for.

31:14.873 --> 31:16.048
[DOOR CLOSES]

31:17.614 --> 31:18.659
[LINE RINGING]

31:18.702 --> 31:20.139
Come on, pick up, pick up.

31:21.183 --> 31:22.881
[LINE CONTINUES RINGING]

31:22.924 --> 31:24.360
ON VOICEMAIL: This is Emily, leave a message.

31:25.405 --> 31:26.841
[SIGHS]

31:34.588 --> 31:35.981
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

31:42.204 --> 31:43.771
EMILY: Hey.

31:43.814 --> 31:46.992
NICK: Hey. Hey, he cleared out his office. He got everything.

31:47.035 --> 31:48.907
He knows we're onto him now.

31:48.950 --> 31:50.473
NICK: The interview's
probably over.

31:53.737 --> 31:54.825
Don't worry.

31:56.697 --> 31:57.916
I got this covered.

32:04.183 --> 32:05.358
[CAR LOCK BEEPS]

32:18.937 --> 32:20.329
[ODUWALE GRUNTING]

32:31.036 --> 32:32.646
ODUWALE: Emily?

32:32.689 --> 32:35.562
You better start talking.

32:35.605 --> 32:38.652
[GROANS] What's going on?
You have any idea
what that is?

32:43.048 --> 32:45.833
Emily, you gotta let me go.

32:45.876 --> 32:47.530
That's Tyler Brandon Mills'

32:47.574 --> 32:49.141
phosgene gas from
the evidence locker...

32:49.184 --> 32:51.186
You've gotta let me go.
Do you know what
he had planned next?

32:52.448 --> 32:53.536
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

32:54.146 --> 32:55.930
He made these.

32:55.974 --> 32:57.845
ODUWALE: Help!
More portable,

32:57.888 --> 32:59.760
so he could take 'em
wherever he wanted.

33:00.456 --> 33:01.675
[GRUNTING]

33:05.896 --> 33:06.941
Emily...

33:08.203 --> 33:09.509
You can't do this.

33:11.163 --> 33:12.816
You're an FBI agent!

33:12.860 --> 33:15.254
I entrusted you
with my son!

33:15.297 --> 33:17.212
I can do whatever
I want to you.

33:26.961 --> 33:28.919
I know Rex Wolfe
was your patient,

33:28.963 --> 33:32.793
and I know you had him inject
at least six people with
some kind of serum.

33:32.836 --> 33:35.100
And then you
had him kill them.

33:35.143 --> 33:37.015
I don't know what
you're talking about!

33:38.581 --> 33:39.669
Bullshit.

33:41.236 --> 33:42.759
Do you know
how phosgene works?

33:43.282 --> 33:44.239
Do you?

33:47.460 --> 33:48.591
Emily, don't do this.

33:50.245 --> 33:51.246
Emily!

33:53.379 --> 33:56.382
Hey. Did Oduwale give up
anything in the interview?

33:56.425 --> 33:58.645
No, no.
He never tripped up.

33:59.602 --> 34:00.734
So where'd you go?

34:02.431 --> 34:03.867
Uh...

34:03.911 --> 34:05.913
Oduwale's office.

34:05.956 --> 34:08.872
Did we get a warrant?
No, and it doesn't
matter anyway.

34:08.916 --> 34:12.050
Someone cleared
the place out.
Probably Oduwale.

34:12.093 --> 34:13.138
Mmm-hmm.

34:14.226 --> 34:16.358
Have you seen Emily?
Is she back?

34:16.402 --> 34:19.187
No. She's not in the office.
She's not answering her phone.

34:19.231 --> 34:20.536
Do you have any idea
where she is?

34:21.146 --> 34:22.147
Fuck.

34:23.626 --> 34:25.367
Dr. Oduwale's house.

34:25.411 --> 34:26.586
We have to leave right now.

34:29.197 --> 34:30.242
Quickly.

34:39.903 --> 34:40.991
Talk.

34:43.342 --> 34:45.474
Emily, don't do this.
I said talk!

34:48.434 --> 34:50.784
Talk!
Emily, please stop.

34:50.827 --> 34:51.828
[ODUWALE HOLDS BREATH]

34:54.353 --> 34:56.006
EMILY: You're gonna have
to breathe eventually.

34:57.356 --> 34:58.835
That's how this gets inside.

35:04.754 --> 35:06.191
[ODUWALE CHOKING]

35:13.937 --> 35:15.069
There you go.

35:15.113 --> 35:17.245
[ODUWALE COUGHING]
There you go.

35:20.074 --> 35:23.425
Is your throat stinging?
Your eyes are, I can tell.

35:23.469 --> 35:25.949
I'd say you have
eight minutes.
Three good ones.

35:27.342 --> 35:28.691
Now that the gas is

35:28.735 --> 35:30.215
inside your lungs, we can
just sit here and wait,

35:30.258 --> 35:34.306
or we could talk and
I can take you to a hospital.

35:34.349 --> 35:36.656
[EXHALES SHARPLY] Help!

35:37.135 --> 35:38.136
[COUGHING]

35:39.615 --> 35:42.401
Help!
Oh, you're coughing.

35:42.444 --> 35:44.316
This is moving faster
than I expected.

35:44.359 --> 35:45.969
It means that the tissue

35:46.013 --> 35:50.148
in your lungs and in your
throat is liquefying.

35:50.191 --> 35:51.410
[CHOKING]
Emily, stop this.

35:52.672 --> 35:54.935
Please...
I am happy
to just let you die.

35:56.415 --> 35:59.766
But I am curious,
why fentanyl?

36:01.159 --> 36:04.684
[STUTTERING]
'Cause I failed.

36:07.121 --> 36:08.209
I failed.

36:10.080 --> 36:14.781
I had to cover all the traces
so that the work could go on.

36:14.824 --> 36:15.999
What failed?

36:16.043 --> 36:17.566
[ODUWALE COUGHING]

36:17.610 --> 36:19.525
What did you inject them with?

36:20.787 --> 36:22.049
A serum.

36:22.832 --> 36:24.182
I developed a serum.

36:25.139 --> 36:27.663
I injected them
with resilience.

36:29.839 --> 36:31.014
And it worked.

36:32.102 --> 36:34.279
It worked perfectly
on Rex Wolfe.

36:36.281 --> 36:38.108
I cured his PTSD.

36:38.152 --> 36:39.893
Is that why he was
an efficient killer?

36:39.936 --> 36:45.072
No, Rex was a soldier,
a disciplined soldier.

36:45.115 --> 36:49.685
But the civilians,
they failed.

36:49.729 --> 36:53.646
They went wrong. Emily.
Please, stop this.

36:53.689 --> 36:57.563
And the gas attack? Did you
inject Tyler Brandon Mills?

36:57.606 --> 36:59.695
Rex took care of that.
And Tommy Gibbs?

36:59.739 --> 37:02.959
For God's sake,
open the window!Was Tommy a mistake too?

37:03.003 --> 37:04.222
He got too close.

37:06.093 --> 37:07.703
How did you develop
the serum?

37:07.747 --> 37:09.096
[COUGHS]

37:14.580 --> 37:17.626
It started with animal trials.

37:18.453 --> 37:20.890
Countless animal trials.

37:21.935 --> 37:23.371
All failures.

37:24.764 --> 37:26.374
I knew that if I was gonna

37:26.418 --> 37:28.898
advance the work, I needed
a human subject. [COUGHS]

37:30.248 --> 37:31.858
But I wouldn't
cross that line.

37:33.860 --> 37:34.948
I couldn't.

37:35.905 --> 37:37.603
Until I got sent a package.

37:39.518 --> 37:40.823
A vial of blood.

37:41.476 --> 37:42.956
No name, no address.

37:44.914 --> 37:46.264
Just a note.

37:46.307 --> 37:48.701
It said, "What do you
think of this?"

37:48.744 --> 37:53.880
That blood had properties
I had never seen.

37:53.923 --> 37:58.145
Way more advanced than the
hormonal compounds I'd found.

37:58.188 --> 38:01.191
And they kept coming,
month after month.

38:02.149 --> 38:03.455
Then I got an email.

38:04.499 --> 38:06.980
"Are you ready to take
the next step?

38:08.286 --> 38:11.680
"Are you ready to meet
the donor patient?"

38:12.986 --> 38:14.379
And the rest you know.

38:16.555 --> 38:17.817
It was Laurie.

38:21.951 --> 38:24.737
She brought me to you.

38:29.307 --> 38:33.093
Your blood was
the genesis of the serum.

38:33.136 --> 38:37.097
You are connected to all
the fentanyl victims.

38:37.140 --> 38:39.882
Your blood was in their veins.

38:51.807 --> 38:53.243
You tortured me.

38:53.287 --> 38:55.855
I made you what you are!

38:55.898 --> 38:58.510
Your resilience got stronger
the longer you were caged.

38:58.553 --> 38:59.772
I did that!

39:08.041 --> 39:09.216
Do you see her car?

39:17.877 --> 39:19.182
Nick.
ODUWALE: No!

39:22.185 --> 39:25.667
That's not phosgene, is it?

39:26.625 --> 39:27.626
Huh?

39:28.366 --> 39:29.584
No, no.

39:30.933 --> 39:32.282
You won't kill me.

39:32.979 --> 39:34.284
You can't kill me.

39:35.373 --> 39:37.418
Not until you know
about Flynn.

39:38.506 --> 39:41.074
Did you inject Flynn?
Untie me!

39:41.770 --> 39:44.947
Did you inject my son?

39:44.991 --> 39:46.079
CAL: Byrne!
NICK: Emily!

39:49.038 --> 39:51.127
[BOTH COUGHING]

39:51.171 --> 39:53.913
What the hell, Byrne?
It's just tear gas.

39:53.956 --> 39:55.218
[EXPLOSION]

39:55.262 --> 39:56.568
NICK: Fire!

39:56.611 --> 39:58.047
Jesus! Outside!

40:07.187 --> 40:08.406
[ALL GROANING]

40:16.152 --> 40:17.719
[COUGHING]

40:18.981 --> 40:20.722
[GRUNTING]

40:20.766 --> 40:21.723
Thank God you're here.

40:22.289 --> 40:24.247
Come on.

40:24.291 --> 40:27.555
Get me outta here before
she comes back. Untie me.
Come on. What are you doing?

40:29.818 --> 40:30.906
CAL: What was that?

40:32.473 --> 40:33.866
[GROANING]

40:54.756 --> 40:58.194
CAL: Oh, my God.
Oduwale's been shot.
